<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,403,383,409]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Observations:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luteyn" authorityYear="2013" box="[403,725,384,409]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Sphyrospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="revolutum">
<emphasis box="[403,725,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Sphyrospermum revolutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by having revolute, slightly bullate and narrowly lanceolate leaves, flowers 5-merous with short-pilose pedicels and calyces, corollas that are glabrous and greenish-cream colored, and 10 stamens. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luteyn" authorityYear="2013" box="[704,1026,461,486]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Sphyrospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="revolutum">
<emphasis box="[704,1026,461,486]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Sphyrospermum revolutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[1187,1374,461,486]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Sphyrospermum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearifolium">
<emphasis box="[1187,1374,461,486]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">S. linearifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(NY isotype sterile) from 
<collectingCountry box="[400,529,500,526]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Morales, J. F. &amp; Rodriguez, A." box="[546,879,500,526]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="335 - 337" refId="ref21303" refString="Morales, J. F. &amp; Rodriguez, A. (2005) Una nueva especie Sphyrospermum (Ericaceae) para Costa Rica. Novon 15: 335 - 337." type="journal article" year="2005">Morales &amp; Rodríguez 2005</bibRefCitation>
); the latter species differs by its more glabrous and non-lianoid habit, non-bullate leaves that are acute apically, much longer pedicels, smaller flowers with white corollas, and fewer stamens. Both species are known only from their 
<typeStatus box="[1122,1176,577,603]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">type</typeStatus>
specimens, so more collections are needed to evaluate the range of the characters and interspecific relationships.
</paragraph>
